# Component structure rules (Pulse UI)

## Props: destructure in function parameters

**Never use `props.something` inside the component.** Destructure in the function signature.

```tsx
// ❌ BAD
export function Card(props: CardProps) {
  const { title } = props;
  return <div>{props.title}</div>;
}

// ✅ GOOD
export function Card({ title, children }: CardProps) {
  return <div>{title}{children}</div>;
}
```

## Custom hooks in separate files

**Never define custom hooks inside component files.** Put them in `use[HookName].ts` under the feature's `hooks/` folder. Hook file naming: `use[HookName].ts` (not `.tsx`). Pure functions (no React hooks) should not be named with `use` prefix.

## One logical component per file

Default: one main component per file. Extract subcomponents when reused, non-trivial, or when the file gets long. Very small helpers (< 5 lines, used only in this file) may stay in the same file, at the bottom after the main component.

## No pure functions in component files

Pure functions (no React hooks, no JSX) belong in utils or constants files, not inside component files. Use constants or utils under the feature (e.g. `RELEASE_STATUS_COLORS` in constants, `getDropZoneClassName` in utils).

## Types in separate files

Prefer `.interface.ts` (or `.types.ts`) in the feature for that feature's types. Inline props only for local-only, simple shapes. Shared types in `src/types/` only when used across features.
